<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="34">
<pageStartToken pageNumber="34">Etymology</pageStartToken>
. Dahl named this species to honor Dr. George Sprague Meyer, an eminent ichthyologist from Stanford University.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="34">
Distribution. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:12762877-CE05-4441-8882-F89312533448" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus myersi Dahl 1958:42" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="myersi">A. myersi</taxonomicName>
is known from the floodplain savannahs of the lower 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Magdalena between Cartagena and Barranquilla Colombia. Its distribution extents inland up the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Magdalena valley (Fig. 1), however, the extent of its distribution is poorly known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
